+### Phase 3 ŌĆö Security Review ­¤¤ó
+
+| Vector | Result | Notes |
+|---|---|---|
+| Hardcoded secrets | **None found** (`grep -rEn 'ghp_\|gho_\|ghs_\|github_pat_\|AKIA[0-9A-Z]{16}\|password\s*=\|secret\s*=\|api[_-]?key\|token\s*='`). | Verified across all `.ps1/.psm1/.psd1/.yml`. |
+| Embedded API keys | None. The module never reads/stores tokens; `gh` owns credentials. | ŌĆö |
+| Authentication flaws | N/A ŌĆö auth is delegated to `git` credential manager and `gh`. | ŌĆö |
+| Authorisation bypasses | N/A ŌĆö local tool. | ŌĆö |
+| Path traversal | `$BaseFolders` is enumerated with `Get-ChildItem -Directory` (not `-Recurse`) and each entry must contain `.git`. No string concatenation into shell commands. | Ō£ģ |
+| Injection vectors | `git` arguments are passed as **arrays** (`Invoke-GitCommand -Arguments @('add','-A')`), so PowerShell parameter binding is used, not shell interpolation. Commit messages are user-supplied but go via `git commit -m $Message` array-form ŌĆö safe. `gh` arguments same. | Ō£ģ |
+| Unsafe deserialisation | No `ConvertFrom-Json -AsHashtable` on untrusted input. No `Import-Clixml`. No `Invoke-Expression`. | Ō£ģ |
+| Logging of sensitive data | `Write-Hacker` writes commit messages and remote URLs to the log. Commit messages may contain user-typed content; remote URLs may contain a username (not a token). **Low risk.** Recommend a `-RedactRemote` opt-in. | Low |
+| Force-push safety | Uses `--force-with-lease` rather than `--force` for non-tag pushes. Ō£ģ |
+| `Set-ExecutionPolicy` advice | README and INSTALLATION recommend `RemoteSigned` (not `Bypass`). Ō£ģ |
